text: Thornwood is an unincorporated community in Skagit County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Thornwood was established in 1900, and remained in operation until 1912. The community derives its name from W. J. Thorne, an early resident. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skagit County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Thornwood, Washington
